Police ID man shot to death in NW Houston
1/9
Back to Gallery
Police have identified a man who was shot to death Monday night outside his family home in northwest Houston.
The shooting happened about 9:15 p.m. in the 7000 block of Cole Creek near Bitternut, according to the Houston Police Department.
Cole Creek Homicide
Media: Metro Video
Police said Victor Saavedra was outside the house while his family was inside the home. When his relatives heard gunfire, they ran outside and found Saavedra wounded. He died at the scene.
Witnesses, police said, told investigators they saw a man speeding away from the scene in a gray Infinity G35 after the gunfire. No other description of the man was available.
So far, investigators have no motive in the shooting.
